Azure Resource Groups
- Logical container to organize Azure resources.
- Resources can be deployed, updated, and deleted together.
- Supports RBAC, Policies, and Tags.
- A resource can belong to only one Resource Group at a time.

Azure Subscription
- Billing and resource management boundary in Azure.
- Used to isolate environments (Dev, QA, Prod).
- Defines quotas and usage limits.
- Resources are deployed under a subscription.
- Multiple subscriptions can exist under one tenant.

Azure Management Groups
- Organize multiple Azure subscriptions hierarchically.
- Apply governance across many subscriptions.
- Policies and RBAC can be inherited.
- Helps large enterprises manage Azure at scale.
- Can have multiple levels of hierarchy.

